Wisconsin: Dirty Voter Rolls, the ERIC Scam, and WEC the Fraud Enabler

The Wisconsin Assembly on Campaigns and Elections held an informational hearing on Wednesday in which Peter Bernegger presented compelling red flag analysis of Wisconsin‚Äôs voter rolls and voter registration system.

Bernegger‚Äôs team, comprised of 1,500 (soon to be 5,500) volunteers across the state, purchased $60K worth of Wisconsin Elections Commission (WEC) statewide and county voter registration lists spanning 4 different dates and secured access to a ‚Äúsuper computer‚Äù to help analyze the data. Here‚Äôs what they‚Äôve found so far:

‚Ä¢ The Wis Vote database has 7.1M registrants despite the fact that the state only has 4M adults (Jeff O‚ÄôDonnell reported the same shocking finding in December).

‚Ä¢ The Wis Vote statewide voter database has never been audited in its 16-year existence.

‚Ä¢ There are ‚Äú625K dead people on the voter rolls statewide and that number grows weekly.‚Äù

‚Ä¢ There are 1M voters with a 1918 registration date (Jeff O‚ÄôDonnell also noticed this ‚Äúglitch‚Äù).

‚Ä¢ The city of Milwaukee alone has 264K voters with a 1918 registration date, 66K deceased voters, and 20K voters at an undeliverable address.

‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúYou can switch an inactive person to active with 2 clicks. It opens the door to fraud. You can flip 100K people, vote them, and flip them back and no one would ever know. We‚Äôve seen how easy it is to do.‚Äù (Jeff O‚ÄôDonnell also noted this capability in his December testimony).  

‚Ä¢ There are tens of thousands of addresses with large excess registrations, including 45K single family homes (for example, 26 people registered to a 2 bedroom apartment).

‚Ä¢ There are thousands of voters with missing or inaccurate key information. For example some have no last name, others are missing a first name or an address, or they have a fake voter ID (a symbol or a word), or an address that doesn‚Äôt exist (like 0 Airport Rd). 

‚Ä¢ The Department of Transportation (DOT aka DMV) could not verify 46K voters who voted in the 2020 election (this issue was also identified by the LAB audit, which released its findings in October). 

‚Ä¢ The team found 1.5M illegally registered voters in the the state, 155K suspected fake voters, and 50K illegally cast ballots ‚Äúthat can be proven.‚Äù

Bernegger then addressed the ERIC voter registration ‚Äúscam.‚Äù

ERIC, the false flag ‚Äúvoter roll accuracy system‚Äù used by 30 states, was funded by a Soros Open Society grant and founded by David Becker, who also founded CEIR, which received $70M from Zuckerberg to help Democrats ‚Äúfortify‚Äù the 2020 election. 

ERIC‚Äôs bylaws effectively require the WEC and election clerks to function as ERIC voter registration drive volunteers. ERIC identifies ‚Äúeligible residents who are not registered to vote,‚Äù and Wisconsin is required ‚Äúat a minimum to initiate contact [with those] citizens and inform them how to register to vote.‚Äù

Who is ERIC registering?

Bernegger pointed out that ERIC recently lost a lawsuit in DC that ruled the conditions imposed by ERIC‚Äôs bylaws are illegal. He also noted that Louisiana has dropped ERIC, Arizona is expected to dump the ERIC system soon, and Florida is pushing to ditch ERIC.   

Bernegger concluded by recommending that WEC be gutted and rebuilt. Their illegal ‚Äúguidance‚Äù enabled fraud. For example WEC:

‚Ä¢ Told clerks to stop counting on election night
‚Ä¢ Declared that drop boxes were legal
‚Ä¢ Decided that clerks could cure ballots
‚Ä¢ Encouraged machine vendors to wipe system logs clean
‚Ä¢ Overruled the requirement for Special Voting Deputies at nursing homes, which protects against ballot harvesting
‚Ä¢ And permitted 46K voters without DOT verification to vote. 

Bernegger‚Äôs team is also investigating: ‚Äúhuman mules,‚Äù drop boxes, indefinitely confined voters, National Vote at Home, and Zuckerberg‚Äôs CTCL.
